<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 08 at 3:50PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Hansford and southwestern Ochiltree Counties through 415 PM CDT...
At 350 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles northwest of Spearman. This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Spearman.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
